Post Office to the Year 1829'' (Harvard University Press, 1924)\n* {{cite journal|jstor=1835049|title=The Colonial Post-Office|journal=The American Historical Review|volume=21|issue=2|pages=258\u2013275|last1=Smith|first1=William|year=1916|doi=10.2307/1835049}}\n* {{cite book|last1=United States Postal Service|title=The United States Postal Service: An American History 1775\u20132006|url=https://about.usps.com/publications/pub100.pdf|date=May 2007|publisher=United States Postal Service|quote=Publication 100|accessdate=2017-03-31}}\n* White, Leonard D. ''The Federalists: A study in administrative history: 1789\u20131801'' (1948), pp 173\u201398\n* White, Leonard D. ''The Jeffersonians: A study in administrative history: 1801\u201329'' (1950), pp 299\u2013335\n* White, Leonard D. ''The Jacksonians: A study in administrative history: 1829\u201361'' (1954), pp 251\u201383\n* White, Leonard D. ''The Republican Era: A study in administrative history: 1869\u20131901'' (1963), pp 257\u201377\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{official website|mobile=https://m.usps.com/}}\n* [https://www.federalregister.gov/agencies/postal-service United States Postal Service] in the [[Federal Register]]\n\n{{United States Postal Service}}\n{{Postal system}}\n{{PostalhistoryAmericas}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:United States Postal Service| ]]\n[[Category:Independent agencies of the United States government|Postal Service]]\n[[Category:Postal organizations]]\n[[Category:Express mail]]\n[[Category:Postal system of the United States]]\n[[Category:1775 establishments in the Thirteen Colonies]]\n[[Category:1971 establishments in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Galendalia", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Postal_Service"}
{"title_page": "Ursula Haverbeck", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image= \n| name          = Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel\n| birth_name    = Ursula Hedwig Meta Wetzel\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1928|11|08}}\n| birth_place   = Winterscheid <small>(today part of [[Gilserberg]])</small>, [[Hesse]], [[Weimar Republic]]\n| nationality   = German\n| occupation    = Author\n| criminal_charge = Holocaust Denial\n| criminal_penalty = 2 years imprisonment\n}}\n\n'''Ursula Hedwig Meta Haverbeck-Wetzel''' (born 8 November 1928) is a German [[author]] from [[Vlotho]], Germany.<ref name=\"SDER\">{{Cite book|title=Strategien der extremen Rechten; Hintergr\u00fcnde \u2013 Analysen \u2013 Antworten|trans-title=Strategies of the extreme Right; Backgrounds - Analysis - Answers|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=K6Je0St5eFYC&pg|volume=|first=Stephan|last=Braun|first2=Alexander|last2=Geisler|first3=Martin|last3=Gerster|publisher=VS Verlag f\u00fcr Sozialwissenschaften|location=Wiesbaden|year=2009|language=German|pages=250\u2013251, 427\u2013429|isbn=9783531159119}}</ref><ref name=\"NVSB\">{{Citation|title=Nieders\u00e4chsische Verfassungsschutzbericht 2012|trans-title=Lower Saxony Protection of the Constitution Report 2012|url=http://www.verfassungsschutz.niedersachsen.de/download/81274/Verfassungsschutzbericht_2012.pdf|volume=|first1=|last1=|publisher=Nieders\u00e4chsische Ministerium f\u00fcr Inneres und Sport (Lower Saxony Ministry of Interior and Sport)|location=Hannover|year=2012|language=German|pages=87, 102, 105, 107|isbn=|accessdate=1 August 2015}}</ref> Since 2004, she has also been the subject of lawsuits and convicted due to her [[Holocaust denial]],<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"NVSB\" /><ref name=\"auto\">[http://daserste.ndr.de/panorama/Der-Holocaust-ist-die-groesste-und-nachhaltigste-Luege-der-Geschichte,holocaustleugner100.html Der Holocaust ist die gr\u00f6\u00dfte und nachhaltigste L\u00fcge der Geschichte\"], auf NDR.de; retrieved, 24 April 2015.</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">[http://www.spiegel.de/politik/deutschland/npd-und-die-holocaust-leugnerin-ursula-haverbeck-a-1030072.html Trotz Verbotsverfahren: Holocaust-Leugnerin sprach bei NPD-Veranstaltung], auf Spiegel.de; retrieved, 24 April 2015.</ref><ref name=\"auto2\">[http://www.juedische-allgemeine.de/article/view/id/21285 Eine L\u00fcge zu viel], auf Juedische-Allgemeine.de; retrieved, 24 April 2015.</ref> which in Germany is a criminal offense.\n\nHer husband was {{ill|Werner Georg Haverbeck|de}}, who during the [[Nazi Germany|Nazi period]] was temporarily engaged in the national leadership of the [[Nazi Party]], founder and director in 1933 of the German {{ill|Imperial Federation of Nation and Homeland|de|3=Reichsbund Volkstum und Heimat}}, as well as writer and publisher, historian, [[Folkloristics|folklorist]] and [[parson]] of [[The Christian Community]].<ref name=\"SDER\" /> From 1982 he was also a scientific advisor of the [[Ecological Democratic Party]] (\u00d6DP).{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\nIn November 2015, at the age of 87, she was sentenced to ten months' imprisonment for Holocaust denial.<ref name=mopo>[http://www.mopo.de/nachrichten/ursula-haverbeck-10-monate-knast-fuer-holocaust-leugnerin--87-,5067140,32399414.html URSULA HAVERBECK 10 Monate Knast f\u00fcr Holocaust-Leugnerin (87)] dated 12 November 2015 at mopo.de, accessed 12 November 2015</ref> Several additional  convictions in the fall of 2016 led to <!-- Appears to be at liberty after sentencing before appeals are heard, see post 2014 section below. -->further such sentences. She has unsuccessfully appealed all sentences,<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://global.handelsblatt.com/politics/how-germany-combats-far-right-extremism-812883 | title=Handelsblatt explains: How Germany Combats Far-Right Extremism}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.radioherford.de/nachrichten/kreis-herford/detailansicht/haverbeck-demnaechst-in-detmold-vor-gericht.html |title = Haverbeck demn\u00e4chst in Detmold vor Gericht}}</ref> since 7 May 2018 she is serving her latest two-year jail sentence after being picked up at her home by German police.<ref>https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/elderly-german-neo-nazi-apprehended-sent-to-prison/2018/05/07/273f4602-5210-11e8-a6d4-ca1d035642ce_story.html</ref>\n\n==Life==\nBorn at Winterscheid (today part of [[Gilserberg]]) in [[Hesse]], Haverbeck-Wetzel, by her own account, lived in [[Sweden]] for four years as a homeland displaced person  (''[[Heimatvertriebene]]'') from [[East Prussia]] and studied pedagogy, philosophy and linguistics, including two years in Scotland. For over fifty years, Haverbeck-Wetzel worked in the political shadow of her husband. After her husband's death in 1999, she took over many of his functions including chair of the international [[adult education]] establishment ''Heimvolkshochschule [[Collegium Humanum]]'' in [[Vlotho]], [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], which they both founded in 1963.<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"NVSB\" /> The ''Collegium Humanum'' was first active in the German [[environmental movement]] and from the early 1980s openly turned to the [[Far-right politics|right-wing extremism]] movement; the establishment was subsequently banned by the [[Federal Ministry of the Interior (Germany)|German Federal Ministry of the Interior]] (''Bundesministerium des Innern'') in 2008.<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"NVSB\" />\n\nFrom 1983 until 1989, Haverbeck-Wetzel was also president of the [[World Union for Protection of Life]] (Section Germany), and disclosed in this [[Non-governmental organization|non-governmental]] position her opposition towards the Western system and the [[Allied-occupied Germany|Allied occupation]] of the [[Federal Republic of Germany]]. She was temporarily a member of the [[Ecological Democratic Party]] (\u00d6DP).<ref>J\u00fcrgen W\u00fcst, Konservatismus und \u00d6kologiebewegung: eine Untersuchung im Spannungsfeld von Partei, Bewegung und Ideologie am Beispiel der \u00d6kologisch-Demokratischen Partei (\u00d6DP), IKO 1993, S. 165</ref> In 1989, at the instigation of the \u00d6DP regional associations [[Bremen]] and [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], she was excluded from the party, amongst other reasons because she attempted to organize a right-wing coalition of the \u00d6DP, [[National Democratic Party of Germany|NPD]], and other groups.<ref>Letters between the branches of \u00d6DP in Bremen and North Rhine-Westphalia 1988-1989 (in German)</ref>\n\nIn 1992, Haverbeck-Wetzel became first chairperson of the newly founded Memorial Sites Association (German: ''Verein Ged\u00e4chtnisst\u00e4tte e.V.''), remaining in that position until 2003.<ref name=\"NVSB\" /> The registered association was established in May 1992 with the statute to build a dignified remembrance for the German civilian victims of [[World War II]] by bombing, abduction, expulsion and detention centres, to end \"the unjustified unilateral nature of the view of history and [[Vergangenheitsbew\u00e4ltigung|struggle to overcome the [negatives of the] past]]\" (German: ''um \"die ungerechtfertigte Einseitigkeit der Geschichtsbetrachtung und Vergangenheitsbew\u00e4ltigung\" zu beenden'').<ref name=\"NVSB\" /> She was a friend of Gudrun Burwitz, Heinrich Himmler's daughter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/nazi-grandma-convicted-denying-holocaust-fifth-time-1643424|title='Nazi grandma' convicted of denying Holocaust for fifth time|last=Baird|first=Roger|date=17 October 2017|work=International Business Times UK|access-date=16 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Right-wing extremism===\nWell before [[German reunification|Germany's reunification]] in 1990, Haverbeck-Wetzel cultivated connections to right-wing political groups like the NPD ([[National Democratic Party of Germany]]) with the aim of a major national collective movement in Germany. This orientation intensified in the years following. It was probably via this path that around 2000 she became acquainted with the Neo-nazi lawyer [[Horst Mahler]]. From this she became active as member and deputy director of the \"Society for the Rehabilitation of Those Persecuted for Refutation of the Holocaust\" (German ''{{ill|Verein zur Rehabilitierung der wegen Bestreitens des Holocaust Verfolgten|de}}''),<ref name=\"NVSB\" /> which was founded in Vlotho on 9 November 2003, the anniversary of [[Kristallnacht]]. Chaired by the Swiss Holocaust denier [[Bernhard Schaub]]. Additionally, almost all well-known Holocaust deniers, including [[Ernst Z\u00fcndel]] (Canada), [[Robert Faurisson]] (France), [[Germar Rudolf]], [[J\u00fcrgen Graf]], [[Gerd Honsik]], [[Wilhelm St\u00e4glich]], [[Gerald Fredrick T\u00f6ben|Fredrick T\u00f6ben]] (Australia), [[Andres Studer]], Hans-Dietrich Sander, [[Manfred Roeder]], [[Frank Rennicke]] and [[Anneliese Remer]] were also involved in its establishment. The organization was subsequently banned in May 2008 by the German Federal Ministry of the Interior (''Bundesministerium des Innern'') on the grounds of being hostile to the constitution of Germany.\n\n===Publication and other offences===\n====From 2004\u201314====\nIn June 2004, the district court of [[Bad Oeynhausen]] sentenced Haverbeck to a \u20ac5,400 fine (180 days at \u20ac30 each) for [[Volksverhetzung|incitement to hatred]] and [[Holocaust denial]].<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"UHWCT\">{{Citation|title=Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel: Einlassung in Bezug auf die Anklage wegen Volksverhetzung in der Begehungsform der Leugnung des Holocaust vor dem Amtsgericht Bad Oeynhausen in der Hauptverhandlung vom 18. Juni 2004|trans-title=Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel: Testimony in relation to the charge of incitement to hatred in the commission form of denial of the Holocaust before the District Court of Bad Oeynhausen in the trial of 18 June 2004|url=http://ursula-haverbeck.info/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Ursula-Haverbeck.pdf|first1=Ursula|last1=Haverbeck-Wetzel|year=2004|language=German}}</ref> In the house journal of the ''Collegium Humanum'', the ''Voice of Conscience'' (''Stimme des Gewissens''), she had introduced a form of denial of the Holocaust,<ref name=\"UHWCT\" /> together with the editor of the magazine, Ernst-Otto Cohrs. The two incriminated publication issues were subsequently confiscated by the German authorities. In a subsequent issue of the Voice of Conscience it was again claimed that the mass destruction of the Jews was \"a myth\". Packaged in a citation by the Russian newspaper ''Russkiy Vestnik'' (''the [[Russian Messenger]]'') who had published in Russia a special revisionist analysis issue of [[J\u00fcrgen Graf]]'s work, with the special ''Russkiy Vestnik'' issue later cited favourably in Moscow's newspaper ''[[Pravda]]'' by Valentin Prussakov,{{fact|date=March 2019}} it was alleged that the number of Jewish victims of [[Nazism|National Socialism]] did not amount to six million, but only about 500,000. On 10 March 2005, the court found a second case against Haverbeck-Wetzel and Cohrs. However, at the request of the [[Bielefeld]] Public [[Prosecutors Office]] the case was closed since \"it was immaterial compared to another\".\n\nAnother article by Haverbeck-Wetzel in the ''Voice of Conscience'' (November/December 2005) posited a thesis that Adolf Hitler was \"just not to be understood from the believed Holocaust or his alleged war obsession, but only by a divine mission in the world-historical context.\" This triggered a renewed process for Holocaust denial, and in June 2007 another fine of 40 days at \u20ac30 euros each by the Dortmund Regional Court.<ref name=\"SDER\" /> Altogether a total fine of \u20ac6,000 (200 days at \u20ac30 each) was formed.\n\nIn June 2009, the District Court of Bad Oeynhausen found Haverbeck-Wetzel guilty of offending [[Charlotte Knobloch]], president of the [[Central Council of Jews in Germany]], who had earlier publicly advocated censorship of the ''Collegium Humanum'' Holocaust-deniers tools.<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"MTB1\">{{cite news |last=Pl\u00f6ger |first=Oliver |date=1 July 2009 |title=Neue Strafe f\u00fcr Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel |trans-title=New penalty for Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel |url=http://www.mt-online.de/lokales/nachbarschaft/bad_oeynhausen/3011548_Neue_Strafe_fuer_Ursula_Haverbeck-Wetzel.html |newspaper=Mindener Tageblatt |location=Minden |language=German |access-date=2 August 2015}}</ref> According to a 1 July 2009 newspaper article in ''{{ill|Mindener Tageblatt|de}}'', Haverbeck-Wetzel wrote in her [[open letter]] response for the attention of Knobloch, among other things, Knobloch should not \"interfere in German domestic affairs\", if Knobloch does not like it in Germany, then she could \"return to her origin in [[Inner Asia]]\", and: \"You do not have to live in Germany - in this evil land, where, as you say, six million of you were gassed.\"<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"MTB1\" /> Her open letter also contained hostility such as \"Prepare yourself for the day of truth. It is near and unstoppable.\", as well as \"I warn you.\"...\"If you continue as before, then a new [[pogrom]] could result, which would be horrific.\"<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"MTB1\" /> Knobloch subsequently filed a criminal complaint, and Haverbeck-Wetzel was sentenced to a fine of \u00ae2,700.<ref name=\"MTB1\" />\n\n====Since 2014====\nIn November 2014, Haverbeck-Wetzel lodged a police complaint against the Central Council of Jews in Germany. She accused the council of \"persecution of innocent people\". The investigation was abandoned in December 2014. The Bielefeld Public Prosecutors Office eventually examined proceedings against Haverbeck-Wetzel for false accusation.<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n\nIn the [[ARD (broadcaster)|ARD]] television broadcast series ''{{ill|Panorama (German TV series)|de|Panorama (Magazin)}}'' produced by [[Norddeutscher Rundfunk|NDR]] in March 2015, and despite proceedings prohibiting, Haverbeck-Wetzel again denied the mass destruction of the Jews and discussed her views.<ref name=\"PMIUHW\">{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WPa_QeV9KDM|title=Ursula Haverbeck: The Panorama Interview, with English Subtitles|date=14 May 2015|work=YouTube}}</ref> She described \"this Holocaust\" as \"the biggest and most persistent lie in history\".<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"PMIUHW\" /><ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.de/2015/04/24/haverbeck-holocaust_n_7133406.html \"Panorama\" zeigt, wie dreist eine 86-j\u00e4hrige NPD-Referentin den Holocaust leugnet], auf HuffingtonPost.de</ref> Haverbeck-Wetzel published a video on [[YouTube]] protesting against the trial of [[Oskar Gr\u00f6ning]], the so-called \"Accountant of Auschwitz\", and distributed leaflets outside the court which were reported to feature Holocaust denial.<ref>{{cite web|last=Saul|first=Heather|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/neonazis-gather-at-trial-of-oskar-groening-and-claim-former-auschwitz-guard-is-a-victim-of-german-justice-system-10192866.html|title=Neo-Nazis gather at trial of Oskar Groening and claim former Auschwitz guard is a 'victim' of German justice system|work=The Independent|date=21 April 2015|accessdate=14 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://daserste.ndr.de/panorama/aktuell/NPD-und-Holocaust-Luege-peinlicher-Auftritt-vor-Auschwitz-Prozess,holocaustleugner112.html|title=NPD und Holocaust-L\u00fcge: Peinlicher Auftritt vor Auschwitz-Prozess|author=NDR|work=ndr.de}}</ref>\n\nHaverbeck-Wetzel became the subject of a new investigation initiated in June 2015 by the Bielefeld Public Prosecutors Office, in connection with a publication in the journal ''The Voice of the Empire'' (''Die Stimme des Reiches''), prompting Haverbeck-Wetzel's home as well as that of three other accused persons to be searched by the State Criminal Police Office of [[Lower Saxony]] (''Landeskriminalamt Niedersachsen'') for evidence.<ref>[http://www.mt.de/lokales/regionales/20476803_Hausdurchsuchung-bei-Holocaust-Leugnerin-Ursula-Haverbeck-in-Vlotho.html \"Hausdurchsuchung bei Holocaust-Leugnerin Ursula Haverbeck in Vlotho\"], auf ''Mindener Tageblatt''; retrieved, 5 June 2015.</ref> In November, after being found guilty, she was sentenced to ten months in prison.<ref name=mopo/><ref>{{cite news|last=Charter|first=David|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/news/world/europe/article4613415.ece|title=German grandmother, 87, jailed for Holocaust denial|work=The Times|location=London|date=13 November 2015|accessdate=14 January 2017}}</ref> In the Hamburg court, she insisted the status of Auschwitz as a place of death is \"not historically proven\" and is \"only a belief\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/germany/11993382/German-Nazi-grandma-sentenced-to-10-months-in-prison-for-Holocaust-denial.html|title=German 'Nazi grandma' sentenced to 10 months in prison for Holocaust denial|work=The Daily Telegraph|location=London|agency=AFP|date=13 November 2015|accessdate=14 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2016, Haverbeck-Wetzel was sentenced to ten months imprisonment for Holocaust denial, without the option for parole, but remained free until an appeal was heard concerning the earlier case. She had written to [[Detmold]]'s mayor, Rainer Heller the previous February insisting Auschwitz was no more than a labor camp and those who survived were only \"alleged witnesses\" following the trial of former Auschwitz [[Schutzstaffel|SS]] guard [[Reinhold Hanning]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/prominent-german-neo-nazi-convicted-of-holocaust-denial/|title=Prominent German neo-Nazi convicted of Holocaust denial|work=The Times of Israel|agency=Associated Press|date=3 September 2016|accessdate=14 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dw.com/en/nazi-grandma-holocaust-denier-ursula-haverbeck-sentenced-to-jail/a-19522941|title='Nazi Grandma' holocaust denier Ursula Haverbeck sentenced to jail|work=DW|location=Germany|agency=AFP|date=2 September 2016|accessdate=14 January 2017}}</ref> In October, she was sentenced to 11 months in Bad Oeynhausen for incitement to hate. In court again, the next month,<!-- November 2016. --> Haverbeck-Wetzel was sentenced in [[Verden an der Aller|Verden]] to 2{{frac|1|2}} more years in jail for Holocaust denial after restating her claims in ''Voice of the Reich'' (''Stimme des Reiches'').<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jta.org/2016/11/23/news-opinion/world/german-holocaust-denier-ursula-haverbeck-88-again-sentenced-to-prison|title=German Holocaust denier Ursula Haverbeck, 88, again sentenced to prison|work=Jewish Telegraph Agency|date=23 November 2016|accessdate=14 January 2017}} Reprinted at {{cite news|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/german-holocaust-denier-again-sentenced-to-prison/|title=German Holocaust denier again sentenced to prison|work=The Times of Israel|date=23 November 2016|accessdate=14 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n\n===Non-fiction===\n\n*Werner G. Haverbeck: ''Der Weltkampf um den Menschen. Eine deutsche Selbstbesinnung'' (The world struggle for the man. A German self-reflection), [[Grabert Verlag]], Tuebingen 1995, {{ISBN|9783878471516}}\n*Werner G. Haverbeck: ''Der Weltkampf um die Gemeinschaft. Die Entwicklung der Demokratie zur Volksordnung'' (The world struggle for the community. The development of democracy into a people's order), Grabert Verlag, T\u00fcbingen 1996, {{ISBN|9783878471547}}\n*with [[Erhard Eppler]], Max Guede (eds.), Walter H\u00e4hnle (pub.): ''Bekommen wir eine andere Republik?'' (Do we get a different republic?), {{ill|Gustav Heinemann Initiative|de}}, Radius-Verlag GmbH, Stuttgart 1982, {{ISBN|9783871735363}}\n*with Martin Black, Claudio Mutti, Wolfgang Sch\u00fcler, Oliver Ritter (eds.): ''Religion und Tradition'' (Religion and Tradition), Verlag Zeitenwende, Dresden 2002, {{ISBN|9783934291157}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{Citation|title=Nieders\u00e4chsische Verfassungsschutzbericht 2012|trans-title=2012 Report of the Lower Saxony State Office for the Protection of the Constitution|url=http://www.verfassungsschutz.niedersachsen.de/download/81274/Verfassungsschutzbericht_2012.pdf|volume=|first1=|last1=|publisher=Nieders\u00e4chsische Ministerium f\u00fcr Inneres und Sport (Lower Saxony Ministry of Interior and Sport)|location=Hannover|year=2012|language=German|pages=87, 102, 105, 107|isbn=}}\n*Phillip Austen: Ursula Haverbeck. The maker of the Collegium Humanum - a portrait In: The right margin, No. 93, March / April 2005.\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://ursula-haverbeck.info/ Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel Official German website]{{in lang|de}}\n* [http://www.publikative.org/2011/01/18/collegium-humanum-braune-ikone-hetzt-weiter/ \"Collegium Humanum\": Braune Ikone hetzt weiter] \"Collegium Humanum\": Brown icon incites further, publikative.org, 18 January 2011\n* [https://www.antifainfoblatt.de/artikel/das-collegium-humanum-%E2%80%93%C2%A0ein-zentrum-der-holocaustleugner Antifaschistisches Info Blatt (AIB) Nr.70/1.2006: ''\"Das Collegium Humanum - Ein Zentrum der Holocaustleugner\"''] Anti-Fascists Fact Sheet No. 70/1.2006: ''\"The Collegium Humanum - A centre of Holocaust deniers\"''\n* [http://www.focus.de/politik/deutschland/holocaust-goettlicher-auftrag_aid_262666.html HOLOCAUST \"G\u00f6ttlicher Auftrag\", Focus Magazine Online, 25. Februar 2008] HOLOCAUST \"Divine Order\", Focus Magazine Online, 25 February 2008\n* [http://www.westfalenblatt.de/nachrichten/regional/herford.php?id=42498&artikel=1 Westfalen Blatt - Holocaust-Leugnerin erneut vor Gericht, 4. Oktober 2010] Westfalen paper - Holocaust-denier again in court, 4 October 2010\n* [http://www.publikative.org/2013/03/30/holocaust-leugnerin-in-der-heide/ Holocaust-Leugnerin in der Heide] Holocaust-denier in the Heide, publikative.org, 30 March 2013\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Historical revisionism}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Haverbeck-Wetzel, Ursula}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Herford (district)]]\n[[Category:German people convicted of Holocaust denial]]\n[[Category:20th-century German writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century German writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century German women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century German women writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| image= \n| name          = Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel\n| birth_name    = Ursula Hedwig Meta Wetzel\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1928|11|08}}\n| birth_place   = Winterscheid <small>(today part of [[Gilserberg]])</small>, [[Hesse]], [[Weimar Republic]]\n| nationality   = German\n| occupation    = Author\n| criminal_charge = Holocaust Denial\n| criminal_penalty = 2 years imprisonment\n}}\n\n'''Ursula Hedwig Meta Haverbeck-Wetzel''' (born 8 November 1928) is a German [[author]] from [[Vlotho]], Germany.<ref name=\"SDER\">{{Cite book|title=Strategien der extremen Rechten; Hintergr\u00fcnde \u2013 Analysen \u2013 Antworten|trans-title=Strategies of the extreme Right; Backgrounds - Analysis - Answers|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=K6Je0St5eFYC&pg|volume=|first=Stephan|last=Braun|first2=Alexander|last2=Geisler|first3=Martin|last3=Gerster|publisher=VS Verlag f\u00fcr Sozialwissenschaften|location=Wiesbaden|year=2009|language=German|pages=250\u2013251, 427\u2013429|isbn=9783531159119}}</ref><ref name=\"NVSB\">{{Citation|title=Nieders\u00e4chsische Verfassungsschutzbericht 2012|trans-title=Lower Saxony Protection of the Constitution Report 2012|url=http://www.verfassungsschutz.niedersachsen.de/download/81274/Verfassungsschutzbericht_2012.pdf|volume=|first1=|last1=|publisher=Nieders\u00e4chsische Ministerium f\u00fcr Inneres und Sport (Lower Saxony Ministry of Interior and Sport)|location=Hannover|year=2012|language=German|pages=87, 102, 105, 107|isbn=|accessdate=1 August 2015}}</ref> Since 2004, she has also been the subject of lawsuits and convicted due to her [[Holocaust denial]],<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"NVSB\" /><ref name=\"auto\">[http://daserste.ndr.de/panorama/Der-Holocaust-ist-die-groesste-und-nachhaltigste-Luege-der-Geschichte,holocaustleugner100.html Der Holocaust ist die gr\u00f6\u00dfte und nachhaltigste L\u00fcge der Geschichte\"], auf NDR.de; retrieved, 24 April 2015.</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">[http://www.spiegel.de/politik/deutschland/npd-und-die-holocaust-leugnerin-ursula-haverbeck-a-1030072.html Trotz Verbotsverfahren: Holocaust-Leugnerin sprach bei NPD-Veranstaltung], auf Spiegel.de; retrieved, 24 April 2015.</ref><ref name=\"auto2\">[http://www.juedische-allgemeine.de/article/view/id/21285 Eine L\u00fcge zu viel], auf Juedische-Allgemeine.de; retrieved, 24 April 2015.</ref> which in Germany is a criminal offense.\n\nHer husband was {{ill|Werner Georg Haverbeck|de}}, who during the [[Nazi Germany|Nazi period]] was temporarily engaged in the national leadership of the [[Nazi Party]], founder and director in 1933 of the German {{ill|Imperial Federation of Nation and Homeland|de|3=Reichsbund Volkstum und Heimat}}, as well as writer and publisher, historian, [[Folkloristics|folklorist]] and [[parson]] of [[The Christian Community]].<ref name=\"SDER\" /> From 1982 he was also a scientific advisor of the [[Ecological-Democratic Party]] (\u00d6DP).{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\nIn November 2015, at the age of 87, she was sentenced to ten months' imprisonment for Holocaust denial.<ref name=mopo>[http://www.mopo.de/nachrichten/ursula-haverbeck-10-monate-knast-fuer-holocaust-leugnerin--87-,5067140,32399414.html URSULA HAVERBECK 10 Monate Knast f\u00fcr Holocaust-Leugnerin (87)] dated 12 November 2015 at mopo.de, accessed 12 November 2015</ref> Several additional  convictions in the fall of 2016 led to <!-- Appears to be at liberty after sentencing before appeals are heard, see post 2014 section below. -->further such sentences. She has unsuccessfully appealed all sentences,<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://global.handelsblatt.com/politics/how-germany-combats-far-right-extremism-812883 | title=Handelsblatt explains: How Germany Combats Far-Right Extremism}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.radioherford.de/nachrichten/kreis-herford/detailansicht/haverbeck-demnaechst-in-detmold-vor-gericht.html |title = Haverbeck demn\u00e4chst in Detmold vor Gericht}}</ref> since 7 May 2018 she is serving her latest 2-year jail sentence after being picked up at her home by German police.<ref>https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/elderly-german-neo-nazi-apprehended-sent-to-prison/2018/05/07/273f4602-5210-11e8-a6d4-ca1d035642ce_story.html</ref>\n\n==Life==\nBorn at Winterscheid (today part of [[Gilserberg]]) in [[Hesse]], Haverbeck-Wetzel, by her own account, lived in [[Sweden]] for four years as a homeland displaced person  (''[[Heimatvertriebene]]'') from [[East Prussia]] and studied pedagogy, philosophy and linguistics, including two years in Scotland. For over fifty years, Haverbeck-Wetzel worked in the political shadow of her husband. After her husband's death in 1999, she took over many of his functions including chair of the international [[adult education]] establishment ''Heimvolkshochschule [[Collegium Humanum]]'' in [[Vlotho]], [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], which they both founded in 1963.<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"NVSB\" /> The ''Collegium Humanum'' was first active in the German [[environmental movement]] and from the early 1980s openly turned to the [[Far-right politics|right-wing extremism]] movement; the establishment was subsequently banned by the [[Federal Ministry of the Interior (Germany)|German Federal Ministry of the Interior]] (''Bundesministerium des Innern'') in 2008.<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"NVSB\" />\n\nFrom 1983 until 1989, Haverbeck-Wetzel was also president of the [[World Union for Protection of Life]] (Section Germany), and disclosed in this [[Non-governmental organization|non-governmental]] position her opposition towards the Western system and the [[Allied-occupied Germany|Allied occupation]] of the [[Federal Republic of Germany]]. She was temporarily a member of the [[Ecological Democratic Party]] (\u00d6DP).<ref>J\u00fcrgen W\u00fcst, Konservatismus und \u00d6kologiebewegung: eine Untersuchung im Spannungsfeld von Partei, Bewegung und Ideologie am Beispiel der \u00d6kologisch-Demokratischen Partei (\u00d6DP), IKO 1993, S. 165</ref> In 1989, at the instigation of the \u00d6DP regional associations [[Bremen]] and [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], she was excluded from the party, amongst other reasons because she attempted to organize a right-wing coalition of the \u00d6DP, [[National Democratic Party of Germany|NPD]], and other groups.<ref>Letters between the branches of \u00d6DP in Bremen and North Rhine-Westphalia 1988-1989 (in German)</ref>\n\nIn 1992, Haverbeck-Wetzel became first chairperson of the newly founded Memorial Sites Association (German: ''Verein Ged\u00e4chtnisst\u00e4tte e.V.''), remaining in that position until 2003.<ref name=\"NVSB\" /> The registered association was established in May 1992 with the statute to build a dignified remembrance for the German civilian victims of [[World War II]] by bombing, abduction, expulsion and detention centres, to end \"the unjustified unilateral nature of the view of history and [[Vergangenheitsbew\u00e4ltigung|struggle to overcome the [negatives of the] past]]\" (German: ''um \"die ungerechtfertigte Einseitigkeit der Geschichtsbetrachtung und Vergangenheitsbew\u00e4ltigung\" zu beenden'').<ref name=\"NVSB\" /> She was a friend of Gudrun Burwitz, Heinrich Himmler's daughter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/nazi-grandma-convicted-denying-holocaust-fifth-time-1643424|title='Nazi grandma' convicted of denying Holocaust for fifth time|last=Baird|first=Roger|date=2017-10-17|work=International Business Times UK|access-date=2017-12-16|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Right-wing extremism===\nWell before [[German reunification|Germany's reunification]] in 1990, Haverbeck-Wetzel cultivated connections to right-wing political groups like the NPD ([[National Democratic Party of Germany]]) with the aim of a major national collective movement in Germany. This orientation intensified in the years following. It was probably via this path that around 2000 she became acquainted with the Neo-nazi lawyer [[Horst Mahler]]. From this she became active as member and deputy director of the \"Society for the Rehabilitation of Those Persecuted for Refutation of the Holocaust\" (German ''{{ill|Verein zur Rehabilitierung der wegen Bestreitens des Holocaust Verfolgten|de}}''),<ref name=\"NVSB\" /> which was founded in Vlotho on 9 November 2003, the anniversary of [[Kristallnacht]]. Chaired by the Swiss Holocaust denier [[Bernhard Schaub]]. Additionally, almost all well-known Holocaust deniers, including [[Ernst Z\u00fcndel]] (Canada), [[Robert Faurisson]] (France), [[Germar Rudolf]], [[J\u00fcrgen Graf]], [[Gerd Honsik]], [[Wilhelm St\u00e4glich]], [[Gerald Fredrick T\u00f6ben|Fredrick T\u00f6ben]] (Australia), [[Andres Studer]], Hans-Dietrich Sander, [[Manfred Roeder]], [[Frank Rennicke]] and [[Anneliese Remer]] were also involved in its establishment. The organization was subsequently banned in May 2008 by the German Federal Ministry of the Interior (''Bundesministerium des Innern'') on the grounds of being hostile to the constitution of Germany.\n\n===Publication and other offences===\n====From 2004\u201314====\nIn June 2004, the district court of [[Bad Oeynhausen]] sentenced Haverbeck to a \u20ac5,400 fine (180 days at \u20ac30 each) for [[Volksverhetzung|incitement to hatred]] and [[Holocaust denial]].<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"UHWCT\">{{Citation|title=Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel: Einlassung in Bezug auf die Anklage wegen Volksverhetzung in der Begehungsform der Leugnung des Holocaust vor dem Amtsgericht Bad Oeynhausen in der Hauptverhandlung vom 18. Juni 2004|trans-title=Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel: Testimony in relation to the charge of incitement to hatred in the commission form of denial of the Holocaust before the District Court of Bad Oeynhausen in the trial of 18 June 2004|url=http://ursula-haverbeck.info/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Ursula-Haverbeck.pdf|first1=Ursula|last1=Haverbeck-Wetzel|year=2004|language=German}}</ref> In the house journal of the ''Collegium Humanum'', the ''Voice of Conscience'' (''Stimme des Gewissens''), she had introduced a form of denial of the Holocaust,<ref name=\"UHWCT\" /> together with the editor of the magazine, Ernst-Otto Cohrs. The two incriminated publication issues were subsequently confiscated by the German authorities. In a subsequent issue of the Voice of Conscience it was again claimed that the mass destruction of the Jews was \"a myth\". Packaged in a citation by the Russian newspaper ''Russkiy Vestnik'' (''the [[Russian Messenger]]'') who had published in Russia a special revisionist analysis issue of [[J\u00fcrgen Graf]]'s work, with the special ''Russkiy Vestnik'' issue later cited favourably in Moscow's newspaper ''[[Pravda]]'' by Valentin Prussakov,{{fact|date=March 2019}} it was alleged that the number of Jewish victims of [[Nazism|National Socialism]] did not amount to six million, but only about 500,000. On 10 March 2005, the court found a second case against Haverbeck-Wetzel and Cohrs. However, at the request of the [[Bielefeld]] Public [[Prosecutors Office]] the case was closed since \"it was immaterial compared to another\".\n\nAnother article by Haverbeck-Wetzel in the ''Voice of Conscience'' (November/December 2005) posited a thesis that Adolf Hitler was \"just not to be understood from the believed Holocaust or his alleged war obsession, but only by a divine mission in the world-historical context.\" This triggered a renewed process for Holocaust denial, and in June 2007 another fine of 40 days at \u20ac30 euros each by the Dortmund Regional Court.<ref name=\"SDER\" /> Altogether a total fine of \u20ac6,000 (200 days at \u20ac30 each) was formed.\n\nIn June 2009, the District Court of Bad Oeynhausen found Haverbeck-Wetzel guilty of offending [[Charlotte Knobloch]], president of the [[Central Council of Jews in Germany]], who had earlier publicly advocated censorship of the ''Collegium Humanum'' Holocaust-deniers tools.<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"MTB1\">{{cite news |last=Pl\u00f6ger |first=Oliver |date=1 July 2009 |title=Neue Strafe f\u00fcr Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel |trans-title=New penalty for Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel |url=http://www.mt-online.de/lokales/nachbarschaft/bad_oeynhausen/3011548_Neue_Strafe_fuer_Ursula_Haverbeck-Wetzel.html |newspaper=Mindener Tageblatt |location=Minden |language=German |access-date=2 August 2015}}</ref> According to the 1 July 2009 newspaper article in ''{{ill|Mindener Tageblatt|de}}'', Haverbeck-Wetzel wrote in her [[open letter]] response for the attention of Knobloch, among other things, Knobloch should not \"interfere in German domestic affairs\", if Knobloch does not like it in Germany, then she could \"return to her origin in [[Inner Asia]]\", and: \"You do not have to live in Germany - in this evil land, where, as you say, six million of you were gassed.\"<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"MTB1\" /> Her open letter also contained hostility such as \"Prepare yourself for the day of truth. It is near and unstoppable.\", as well as \"I warn you.\"...\"If you continue as before, then a new [[pogrom]] could result, which would be horrific.\"<ref name=\"SDER\" /><ref name=\"MTB1\" /> Knobloch subsequently filed a criminal complaint, and Haverbeck-Wetzel was sentenced to a fine of 2,700 euro.<ref name=\"MTB1\" />\n\n====Since 2014====\nIn November 2014, Haverbeck-Wetzel lodged a police complaint against the Central Council of Jews in Germany. She accused the council of \"persecution of innocent people\". The investigation was abandoned in December 2014. The Bielefeld Public Prosecutors Office eventually examined proceedings against Haverbeck-Wetzel for false accusation.<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n\nIn the [[ARD (broadcaster)|ARD]] television broadcast series ''{{ill|Panorama (German TV series)|de|Panorama (Magazin)}}'' produced by [[Norddeutscher Rundfunk|NDR]] in March 2015, and despite proceedings prohibiting, Haverbeck-Wetzel again denied the mass destruction of the Jews and discussed her views.<ref name=\"PMIUHW\">{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WPa_QeV9KDM|title=Ursula Haverbeck: The Panorama Interview, with English Subtitles|date=14 May 2015|work=YouTube}}</ref> She described \"this Holocaust\" as \"the biggest and most persistent lie in history\".<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"PMIUHW\" /><ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.de/2015/04/24/haverbeck-holocaust_n_7133406.html \"Panorama\" zeigt, wie dreist eine 86-j\u00e4hrige NPD-Referentin den Holocaust leugnet], auf HuffingtonPost.de</ref> Haverbeck-Wetzel published a video on [[YouTube]] protesting against the trial of [[Oskar Gr\u00f6ning]], the so-called \"Accountant of Auschwitz\", and distributed leaflets outside the court which were reported to feature Holocaust denial.<ref>{{cite web|last=Saul|first=Heather|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/neonazis-gather-at-trial-of-oskar-groening-and-claim-former-auschwitz-guard-is-a-victim-of-german-justice-system-10192866.html|title=Neo-Nazis gather at trial of Oskar Groening and claim former Auschwitz guard is a 'victim' of German justice system|work=The Independent|date=April 21, 2015|accessdate=January 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://daserste.ndr.de/panorama/aktuell/NPD-und-Holocaust-Luege-peinlicher-Auftritt-vor-Auschwitz-Prozess,holocaustleugner112.html|title=NPD und Holocaust-L\u00fcge: Peinlicher Auftritt vor Auschwitz-Prozess|author=NDR|work=ndr.de}}</ref>\n\nHaverbeck-Wetzel became the subject of a new investigation initiated in June 2015 by the Bielefeld Public Prosecutors Office, in connection with a publication in the journal ''The Voice of the Empire'' (''Die Stimme des Reiches''), prompting Haverbeck-Wetzel's home as well as that of three other accused persons to be searched by the State Criminal Police Office of [[Lower Saxony]] (''Landeskriminalamt Niedersachsen'') for evidence.<ref>[http://www.mt.de/lokales/regionales/20476803_Hausdurchsuchung-bei-Holocaust-Leugnerin-Ursula-Haverbeck-in-Vlotho.html \"Hausdurchsuchung bei Holocaust-Leugnerin Ursula Haverbeck in Vlotho\"], auf ''Mindener Tageblatt''; retrieved, 5 June 2015.</ref> In November, after being found guilty, she was sentenced to ten months in prison.<ref name=mopo/><ref>{{cite news|last=Charter|first=David|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/news/world/europe/article4613415.ece|title=German grandmother, 87, jailed for Holocaust denial|work=The Times|location=London|date=November 13, 2015|accessdate=January 14, 2017}}</ref> In the Hamburg court, she insisted the status of Auschwitz as a place of death is \"not historically proven\" and is \"only a belief\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/germany/11993382/German-Nazi-grandma-sentenced-to-10-months-in-prison-for-Holocaust-denial.html|title=German 'Nazi grandma' sentenced to 10 months in prison for Holocaust denial|work=The Daily Telegraph|location=London|agency=AFP|date=November 13, 2015|accessdate=January 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2016, Haverbeck-Wetzel was sentenced to ten months imprisonment for Holocaust denial, without the option for parole, but remained free until an appeal was heard concerning the earlier case. She had written to [[Detmold]]'s mayor, Rainer Heller the previous February insisting Auschwitz was no more than a labor camp and those who survived were only \"alleged witnesses\" following the trial of former Auschwitz [[Schutzstaffel|SS]] guard [[Reinhold Hanning]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/prominent-german-neo-nazi-convicted-of-holocaust-denial/|title=Prominent German neo-Nazi convicted of Holocaust denial|work=The Times of Israel|agency=Associated Press|date=September 3, 2016|accessdate=January 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dw.com/en/nazi-grandma-holocaust-denier-ursula-haverbeck-sentenced-to-jail/a-19522941|title='Nazi Grandma' holocaust denier Ursula Haverbeck sentenced to jail|work=DW|location=Germany|agency=AFP|date=September 2, 2016|accessdate=January 14, 2017}}</ref> In October, she was sentenced to 11 months in Bad Oeynhausen for incitement to hate. In court again, the next month,<!-- November 2016. --> Haverbeck-Wetzel was sentenced in [[Verden an der Aller|Verden]] to 2{{frac|1|2}} more years in jail for Holocaust denial after restating her claims in ''Voice of the Reich'' (''Stimme des Reiches'').<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jta.org/2016/11/23/news-opinion/world/german-holocaust-denier-ursula-haverbeck-88-again-sentenced-to-prison|title=German Holocaust denier Ursula Haverbeck, 88, again sentenced to prison|work=Jewish Telegraph Agency|date=November 23, 2016|accessdate=January 14, 2017}} Reprinted at {{cite news|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/german-holocaust-denier-again-sentenced-to-prison/|title=German Holocaust denier again sentenced to prison|work=The Times of Israel|date=November 23, 2016|accessdate=January 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n\n===Non-fiction===\n\n*Werner G. Haverbeck: ''Der Weltkampf um den Menschen. Eine deutsche Selbstbesinnung'' (The world struggle for the man. A German self-reflection), [[Grabert Verlag]], Tuebingen 1995, {{ISBN|9783878471516}}\n*Werner G. Haverbeck: ''Der Weltkampf um die Gemeinschaft. Die Entwicklung der Demokratie zur Volksordnung'' (The world struggle for the community. The development of democracy into a people's order), Grabert Verlag, T\u00fcbingen 1996, {{ISBN|9783878471547}}\n*with [[Erhard Eppler]], Max Guede (eds.), Walter H\u00e4hnle (pub.): ''Bekommen wir eine andere Republik?'' (Do we get a different republic?), {{ill|Gustav Heinemann Initiative|de}}, Radius-Verlag GmbH, Stuttgart 1982, {{ISBN|9783871735363}}\n*with Martin Black, Claudio Mutti, Wolfgang Sch\u00fcler, Oliver Ritter (eds.): ''Religion und Tradition'' (Religion and Tradition), Verlag Zeitenwende, Dresden 2002, {{ISBN|9783934291157}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{Citation|title=Nieders\u00e4chsische Verfassungsschutzbericht 2012|trans-title=2012 Report of the Lower Saxony State Office for the Protection of the Constitution|url=http://www.verfassungsschutz.niedersachsen.de/download/81274/Verfassungsschutzbericht_2012.pdf|volume=|first1=|last1=|publisher=Nieders\u00e4chsische Ministerium f\u00fcr Inneres und Sport (Lower Saxony Ministry of Interior and Sport)|location=Hannover|year=2012|language=German|pages=87, 102, 105, 107|isbn=}}\n*Phillip Austen: Ursula Haverbeck. The maker of the Collegium Humanum - a portrait In: The right margin, No. 93, March / April 2005.\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://ursula-haverbeck.info/ Ursula Haverbeck-Wetzel Official German website]{{in lang|de}}\n* [http://www.publikative.org/2011/01/18/collegium-humanum-braune-ikone-hetzt-weiter/ \"Collegium Humanum\": Braune Ikone hetzt weiter] \"Collegium Humanum\": Brown icon incites further, publikative.org, 18 January 2011\n* [https://www.antifainfoblatt.de/artikel/das-collegium-humanum-%E2%80%93%C2%A0ein-zentrum-der-holocaustleugner Antifaschistisches Info Blatt (AIB) Nr.70/1.2006: ''\"Das Collegium Humanum - Ein Zentrum der Holocaustleugner\"''] Anti-Fascists Fact Sheet No. 70/1.2006: ''\"The Collegium Humanum - A centre of Holocaust deniers\"''\n* [http://www.focus.de/politik/deutschland/holocaust-goettlicher-auftrag_aid_262666.html HOLOCAUST \"G\u00f6ttlicher Auftrag\", Focus Magazine Online, 25. Februar 2008] HOLOCAUST \"Divine Order\", Focus Magazine Online, 25 February 2008\n* [http://www.westfalenblatt.de/nachrichten/regional/herford.php?id=42498&artikel=1 Westfalen Blatt - Holocaust-Leugnerin erneut vor Gericht, 4. Oktober 2010] Westfalen paper - Holocaust-denier again in court, 4 October 2010\n* [http://www.publikative.org/2013/03/30/holocaust-leugnerin-in-der-heide/ Holocaust-Leugnerin in der Heide] Holocaust-denier in the Heide, publikative.org, 30 March 2013\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Historical revisionism}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Haverbeck-Wetzel, Ursula}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Herford (district)]]\n[[Category:German people convicted of Holocaust denial]]\n[[Category:20th-century German writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century German writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century German women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century German women writers]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ursula_Haverbeck"}
